# **Part 2**

## **Describe your favourite childhood friend.**

One of my favourite childhood friends is a boy named Chen Hao, who was actually my neighbour when I was in primary school. We first met when we were around seven or eight years old because our families lived in the same apartment building. Since we were about the same age, we naturally became close friends very quickly.

Back then, we spent a huge amount of time together almost every day. After school, we would often play football downstairs with other kids in the neighbourhood, and during weekends we sometimes played video games or rode bicycles around the community. As we got older, we also studied together quite often. I still remember preparing for exams with him in the library and helping each other solve maths problems. Even though we were both competitive students, our friendship never became uncomfortable or stressful.

What I liked most about him was probably his personality. He was the kind of person who was always optimistic and energetic. Even when things went wrong, he rarely complained and usually tried to make other people laugh instead. Another thing I admired was that he was very loyal as a friend. For example, whenever I had difficulties in study or felt stressed, he was always willing to listen and encourage me.

Although we don’t see each other as often nowadays because we study in different cities, we still keep in touch online from time to time. Honestly, I think childhood friendships are really special because they are usually very pure and sincere. Whenever I think about my childhood memories, he’s definitely one of the first people that comes to mind.

---

## **中文翻译：**

我最喜欢的一位童年朋友叫陈浩，他其实是我小学时候的邻居。我们大概七八岁时认识，因为住在同一栋楼里。由于年龄差不多，我们很快就成了好朋友。

那时候我们几乎每天都待在一起。放学后，我们经常和小区里的孩子一起踢足球，周末有时候会玩电子游戏或者骑自行车。后来长大一点后，我们也经常一起学习。我还记得我们一起在图书馆复习考试、互相讨论数学题。虽然我们学习上有竞争，但友情从来没有变得尴尬。

我最喜欢他的一点是他的性格。他总是非常乐观、有活力。即使遇到不顺心的事情，他也很少抱怨，反而会想办法让别人开心。另外，他是一个特别讲义气的人。当我学习压力大或者遇到困难时，他总愿意听我倾诉并鼓励我。

虽然现在因为在不同城市读书，我们见面的机会少了很多，但还是会偶尔在网上联系。我觉得童年友谊很特别，因为那种感情通常非常单纯、真诚。每当我回忆童年时，他一定是我最先想到的人之一。

